    <sys:String x:Key="DevHome_desc">Control center for developers to set up environments and track GitHub tasks.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="WindowsTerminal_desc">A modern host for command-line tools like Command Prompt, PowerShell, and WSL.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LinkedIn_desc">Professional networking shortcut to manage your profile and job searches.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="WebMediaExtensions_desc">Adds support for modern web formats like OGG, Vorbis, and Theora.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="OneConnect_desc">Tool for finding and connecting to cellular data plans from your device.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Edge_desc">The default Chromium-based web browser for fast and secure browsing.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Edge_DevTools_desc">A standalone developer toolset for debugging and inspecting web content within Microsoft Edge.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Notepad_desc">The classic lightweight text editor for simple coding and note-taking.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Calculator_desc">Advanced tool for basic, scientific, and programming calculations.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Copilot_desc">AI-powered assistant for answering questions and automating system tasks.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="WhiteBoard_desc">Infinite digital canvas for collaborative brainstorming and ideation.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Wallet_desc">Store digital passes, loyalty cards, and payment information securely.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Spotify_desc">Stream millions of songs and podcasts from your desktop.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="WhatsApp_desc">Desktop version of the popular messaging app for encrypted chats and calls.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Facebook_desc">The official Facebook client. It frequently runs background services for notifications and synchronization, which can consume system memory and battery.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Hulu_desc">Streaming service app for movies and TV shows. If you prefer using a web browser for streaming, this app can be safely removed to free up disk space.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Disney_desc">Official app for Disney+ streaming. Safe to uninstall if you do not have a subscription or prefer streaming via browser.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Instagram_desc">Social media client for photo and video sharing. Like other Meta apps, it often stays active in the background to fetch updates.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Twitter_desc">The official X (Twitter) client for Windows. Provides real-time notifications but can be replaced by the web version to reduce background processes.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TikTok_desc">Official TikTok client. Known for high resource usage during video playback and maintaining persistent background data connections.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="MicrosoftSway_desc">A Microsoft Office app used for creating interactive reports and presentations. Safe to remove if you use the web version or standard PowerPoint.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Builder3D_desc">A tool for viewing, preparing, and printing 3D models. Unless you are involved in 3D modeling or 3D printing, this app is rarely needed.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Netflix_desc">Official Netflix application. While it supports offline downloads, it takes up significant space and remains active for background updates.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="YandexMusic_desc">Streaming music client for Yandex. Freeing up space by removing this is recommended if you use alternative streaming services.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Viber_desc">VoIP and instant messaging application. It is often configured to start with Windows, consuming startup resources and system RAM.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Messaging_desc">A legacy Microsoft app used for basic text messaging on devices with cellular data. Most PC users find this app completely redundant.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Picsart_desc">AI-powered photo and video editor. It has a large install footprint and includes multiple background tasks for cloud synchronization.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Plex_desc">Media player for Plex servers. If you do not manage a local media library or use a Plex server, this app serves no purpose.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="PrimeVideo_desc">Amazon's streaming client. Uninstalling this is safe for users who prefer the browser interface or do not use Amazon Prime.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Shazam_desc">Music identification tool. Since music recognition is often built into browsers and virtual assistants, this separate app is often unnecessary.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="TuneInRadio_desc">Global radio streaming app. Safe to remove to declutter your system if you listen to music through other platforms.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="iHeartRadio_desc">Radio and podcast platform. It maintains a large cache and can impact network performance with background content pre-loading.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="Pandora_desc">Personalized radio service. Recommend removal if the service is not available in your region or if you use Spotify/YouTube Music.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="DolbyAccess_desc">Used to configure Dolby Atmos for headphones or home theaters. Remove only if you do not have compatible hardware or a Dolby license.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="MicrosoftJournal_desc">An ink-focused note-taking application designed for touch and pen devices.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="PowerToys_desc">Advanced system utilities. May increase background RAM usage and CPU wakeups due to multiple active processes.</sys:String>

